      "related": [],
      "cross_links": [
        "math.linalg.matrix-multiplication"
      ],
      "description": "A set R with two operations (+,\u00b7) where (R,+) is an abelian group, \u00b7 is associative, and \u00b7 distributes over +. Commutative ring: ab=ba. Examples: \u2124, \u2124\u2099, polynomial rings, matrices. Unity 1 if present makes a unital ring.",
      "difficulty": "advanced",
      "estimated_hours": 5,
      "bloom": "understand",
      "mastery_threshold": 0.85,
      "references": [
        "Dummit & Foote, Abstract Algebra, Ch.7"
