      "description": "A subset I\u2286R such that (I,+)\u2264(R,+) and for all r\u2208R, i\u2208I: ri\u2208I and ir\u2208I. Quotient ring R/I is well-defined iff I is an ideal. Principal ideal \u27e8a\u27e9={ra:r\u2208R} generated by one element.",
      "difficulty": "expert",
      "estimated_hours": 5,
      "bloom": "apply",
      "mastery_threshold": 0.85,
      "references": [
